conversation.message:
Hello Parent_D—thanks for reaching out. I’m happy to share more.

**Program fit / what we prioritize in families**
We do best with families who value a play-based, socially rich early-years environment and who partner with us through consistent routines, open communication, and alignment on positive guidance. We also look for:
- Clear, timely communication (drop-off/pick-up, changes, health updates)
- Respect for our community norms (kindness, inclusion, collaboration)
- Willingness to work with us on transitions (separation, toileting, naps) and any support plans if needed

**Admissions process & timeline**
If you decide we’re a strong fit, the best next step is a brief application and a short family chat/visit (if available) so we can confirm needs (schedule, allergies, support, etc.). Once we have that, we can typically make a decision quickly.

**Will the spot fill quickly / time to consider**
We do expect our single remaining spot to move fairly soon once families start applying, but we also want families to feel confident. If we extend an offer, we usually allow a short consideration window (e.g., a couple of days) to confirm—so there is time to think, but it isn’t open-ended.

To help me advise you accurately: what’s your child’s age, your needed hours (standard day vs. extended care), and any key needs (allergies, nap routine, language support)? If you’re comfortable sharing, what are you hoping to see most in a nursery this year (social confidence, school readiness, outdoor time, etc.)?
